url: "https://snn.ahkhan.me"
abstract: >
  snn_opt is a Python implementation of a spiking neural network (SNN) inspired
  solver for constrained convex optimization. It targets quadratic and linear
  programs of the form min (1/2) x^T A x + b^T x subject to C x + d <= 0, by
  alternating gradient descent steps with discrete boundary projections — the
  optimization equivalent of leaky integrate-and-fire dynamics with constraint
  spikes. The framework follows Mancoo, Boerlin and Machens (NeurIPS 2020).
keywords:
  - "spiking neural networks"
  - "convex optimization"
  - "quadratic programming"
  - "neuromorphic computing"
  - "constrained optimization"
  - "projected gradient"
